NAME
    Acme::Then - The do-this-then-do-that utility

INSTALLATION
    To install this module, run the following commands:

        perl Makefile.PL
        make
        make test
        make install

SYNOPSIS
        Acme::Then::do {
            ...
        } then {
            ...
            LAST if ...;
        } then {
            ...
        } done;

    You can turn a callback chain

        do_something(cb => sub {
            do_something(cb => sub {
                do_something(cb => sub {
                    my ($res) = @_;
                    say $res;
                });
            });
        });

    into

        Acme::Then::do {
            do_something(cb => NEXT);
        } then {
            do_something(cb => NEXT);
        } then {
            do_something(cb => NEXT);
        } then {
            my ($res) = @_;
            say $res;
        } done;

DESCRIPTION
    Do this, then do that.

FUNCTIONS
  do
    do {} then {} done;

  then
    do {} then {} done;

  done
    do {} then {} done;

  LAST
    Exits from a do-then-done construct.

  NEXT
    Returns a coderef. The arguments to the coderef are set to the next
    block's @_. The coderef should not be called more than once within the
    same block.

AUTHOR
    Tomoki Aonuma <uasi@cpan.org>

